  Goodness is better than beauty Wherever you may be let your wind go free Half a loaf is better than no bread  A wise son brings joy to his father,but a foolish son grief to his mother. Cut your coat according to your cloth Admiration is the daughter of ignorance In for a penny, in for a pound Middle age is when broadness of the mind and narrowness of the waist change places  Lightning never strikes twice in the same place The Absent are Always Wrong Any fool can criticise, condemn and complain and most fools do 
  They that walk much in the sun will be tanned at last One volunteer is worth ten pressed men Abundance, like want, ruins many. Silence is golden.Like flogging a dead horse Nah tek yuh mattie eye fuh see. Distance makes the heart grow fonder Life is a mystery to be lived, not a problem to be solved A tidy house holds a bored woman. 
